<BaseLayout
  title="Why Move Pick-to-Voice to Android? — VPick+"
  description="Why modern pick-to-voice runs on Android: hardware choice, MDM, cost, flexibility, integrations, and future-readiness."
>
  <nav class="breadcrumb container" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a><span class="separator">›</span>
    <a href="/learn">Learn</a><span class="separator">›</span>
    <span aria-current="page">Why Move Pick-to-Voice to Android?</span>
  </nav>

  <section>
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h1 class="section-title">Why Move Pick-to-Voice to Android?</h1>
      <p class="section-sub">Open hardware ecosystem, predictable management, and lower TCO.</p>

      <h2>Key reasons</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Hardware choice:</strong> Rugged handhelds, wearables, enterprise smartphones.</li>
        <li><strong>MDM/EMM:</strong> Enroll, configure Wi-Fi, push updates, and manage at scale.</li>
        <li><strong>Cost:</strong> Avoid proprietary lock-ins; select devices per site needs.</li>
        <li><strong>Integrations:</strong> Modern API patterns to WMS/ERP and services.</li>
        <li><strong>Future-readiness:</strong> Flexibility to adapt devices without rewriting your workflows.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>VPick+ is Android-native by design, enabling voice, screen, and scan on the same device — plus <a href="/learn/scan-driven-mute-mode">SilentScan™</a> for loud areas.</p>

      <div class="card" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <strong>See also:</strong>
        <ul class="list">
          <li><a href="/learn/devices-for-voice-picking">What Devices Work with Pick-to-Voice?</a></li>
          <li><a href="/leasing">VPlus Device Leasing</a> — devices preconfigured with VPick+, VPlus, or VPlus Lite.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p style="margin-top:1.5rem">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/vpick">Explore VPick+ Product</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/contact" style="margin-left:8px;">Talk to Us</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <CtaBand />
</BaseLayout>
